g231\">Roger Griffin, Matthew Feldman. Fascism: The nature of fascism. Routledge, 2004. p. 231.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"rop87\">Robert O. Paxton. ''The Anatomy of Fascism''. New York; Toronto: Random House, Inc., 2005 p. 87.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"rop88\">Robert O. Paxton. ''The Anatomy of Fascism''. New York; Toronto: Random House, Inc., 2005 p. 88.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"rop90\">Robert O. Paxton. ''The Anatomy of Fascism''. New York; Toronto: Random House, Inc., 2005 p. 90.</ref>\n\n<!-- <ref name=\"rosenwein\">Hunt, Lynn, Thomas R. Martin, Barbara H. Rosenwein, R. Po-chia Hsia, and Bonnie G. Smith. The Making of the West: Peoples and Cultures. 2nd ed. Vol. C. Boston: Bedford St. Martins, 2005. p. 1064.</ref> -->\n\n<!-- <ref name=\"routeledge\">Mosse, G: \"Toward a General Theory of Fascism\", ''Fascism'', ed. Griffin (Routeledge) 2003</ref> -->\n\n<ref name=\"routledge12\">Stanley G. Payne. ''A history of fascism, 1914\u20131945''. Digital printing edition. Oxon, England: Routledge, 1995, 2005. pp. 23\u201324.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"routledge13\">Stanley G. Payne. ''A history of fascism, 1914\u20131945''. Digital printing edition. Oxon, England: Routledge, 1995, 2005. p. 24.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"routledge14\">Stanley G. Payne. ''A history of fascism, 1914\u20131945''. Digital printing edition. Oxon, England: Routledge, 1995, 2005. p. 29.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"routledge15\">Stanley G. Payne. ''A history of fascism, 1914\u20131945''. Digital printing edition. Oxon, England: Routledge, 1995, 2005. pp. 24\u201325.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"routledge16\">Stanley G. Payne. ''A history of fascism, 1914\u20131945''. Digital printing edition. Oxon, England: Routledge, 1995, 2005. p. 25.</ref>\n\n<!-- <ref name=\"routledge17\">Peter Davies, Derek Lynch. ''The Routledge companion to fascism and the far right''. London; New York: Routledge. p. 94.</ref> -->\n\n<ref name=\"routledge42\">Stanley G. Payne. ''A history of fascism, 1914\u20131945''. Digital printing edition. Oxon, England: Rou