 weight       = '''G4 Play''': {{convert|137|g|oz|abbr=on}} <br/> '''G4''', '''G4 Plus''': {{convert|155|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| display      = '''G4 Play''': 5.0\" (127 mm) 1280 x 720 (294 [[Pixel density|ppi]]) [[720p]] <br/> '''G4''', '''G4 Plus''': 5.5\" (140 mm) 1920 x 1080 (401 [[Pixel density|ppi]]) [[1080p]] with [[Corning Inc.|Corning]] [[Gorilla Glass]] 3\n| storage      = {{unbulleted list|8 or 16 GB (Moto G4 Play)|16 or 32 GB (Moto G4)| 16, 32 or 64 GB (Moto G4 Plus)}} All 3 models are expandable via microSD card slot\n| memory_card  = [[SDXC|microSDXC]] up to 128 [[Gigabyte|GB]]\n| battery      = {{unbulleted list|2800&nbsp;[[Ampere-hour|mAh]] [[Lithium polymer battery|Li-po]] removable (Moto G4 Play)|3000&nbsp;[[Ampere-hour|mAh]] [[Lithium-ion battery|Li-ion]] non-removable (Moto G4 and Moto G4 Plus)}}\n| type         = [[Smartphone]]\n| form         = [[Slate phone|Slate]]\n| rear_camera  = 13&nbsp;[[megapixel|MP]] (16 MP on Moto G4 Plus), '''''f'''''2.0 [[aperture]], dual [[Correlated color temperature|CCT]] dual tone flash, [[1080p]] video recording @ 30[[Frame rate|fps]], and slow motion record\n| front_camera = 5&nbsp;MP, '''''f'''''2.2\n| connectivity = Micro USB, 3.5&nbsp;mm headset jack\n| sound        = Front-ported loud speaker, 2-Mics\n| released     = {{Start date|2016|05|17}}\n| website      = http://www.motorola.com/us/products/moto-g-family\n}}\n\n'''Moto G4'''  is a line of  [[Android (operating system)|Android]] [[smartphone]]s manufactured by [[Motorola Mobility]], a division of [[Lenovo]]. They are the successor to the [[Moto G (3rd generation)|third-generation Moto G]], and were first released in [[Brazil]] and [[India]] on May 17, 2016, with the other markets following.<ref name=\"ars-motog4\" />\n\nIn comparison to the previous singular Moto G models, the G4 fragmented the line into three models, with the base model joined by a low-end '''Moto G4 Play''' and a higher-end '''Moto G4 Plus''' with an upgraded camera and a fingerprint reader.\n\n==Specifications==\n[[File:Moto G4 Plus Camera.jpg|250px|thumb|Moto G4 Plus Camera 16 MP dual-pixel]]\nThe Moto G4's hardware design was refreshed featuring a \"water repellent nano-coating\", and a camera protrusion. However, unlike the Moto G3, the previous generation the Moto G4 Plus does not feature [[IPX7]] certification. The G4 was available in black and white-colored versions, with different rear-cover and accent-colors available for custom order via MotoMaker. The G4 includes a 5.5-inch 1080p display, an octa-core [[Qualcomm Snapdragon]] 617 system-on-chip, and 2/3&nbsp;GB of RAM. The Moto G4 includes either 16 or 32&nbsp;GB of internal storage, expandable via [[MicroSD]]. It has a 13-megapixel rear-facing camera and a 5-megapixel front-facing camera. The Moto G4 also supports [[802.11n]] Wi-Fi connectivity and an FM radio receiver.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zdnet.com/product/motorola-moto-g4-play/|title=Moto G4 Play review: The best $150 you can spend on a modern Android smartphone|website=ZDNet|access-date=2016-09-20}}</ref><ref name=\"verge-g4\"/>\n\nThe devices shipped with [[Android Marshmallow|Android 6.0.1 \"Marshmallow\"]].<ref name=\"verge-g4\">{{cite web|title=Lenovo fragments Moto G into three models, because it has no idea what we want|url=https://www.theverge.com/2016/5/17/11688790/moto-g-plus-play-release-date-prices-specs-features|website=The Verge|publisher=Vox Media|accessdate=17 May 2016}}</ref> Motorola stated that the Moto G4 line would receive occasional security patches.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2016/07/motorola-confirms-that-it-will-not-commit-to-monthly-security-patches/|title=Motorola confirms that it will not commit to monthly security patches|last=Amadeo|first=Ron|date=2016-07-26|website=Ars Technica|language=en-us|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref> On December 29, 2016, Motorola began rolling out an update to [[Android Nougat|Android 7.0 \"Nougat\"]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gsmarena.com/android_70_nougat_update_starts_hitting_motorola_moto_g4_and_moto_g4_plus-news-21215.php|title=Android 7.0 Nougat update starts hitting Motorola Moto G4 and Moto G4 Plus|website=GSMArena.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref> In September 2017, Motorola stated that the Moto G4 Plus would receive an update to [[Android Oreo|Android 8.1 \"Oreo\"]], although no estimated date was given. An Android 8.1 update was released in February 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.phonearena.com/news/Moto-G4-Plus-Android-Oreo-update_id113555|title=Android 8.1 Oreo finally arrives for the Moto G4 Plus in the U.S.|last=Vasile|first=Cosmin|website=PhoneArena|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n==Alternative Android-ROMs==\n\nOfficial alternative Android-ROMs<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wiki.lineageos.org/devices/athene|title=Info about athene|website=LineageOS}}</ref> for all three G4 models were released by [[LineageOS]], and their support ended<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.xda-developers.com/lineageos-drops-support-devices-inactive-maintainers/|title=LineageOS drops support for multiple devices due to inactive maintainers|website=xda-developers}}</ref> with the final version 14.1 (corresponds to Android 7.1) of September 2018. Other AOSP ROMs up to Android Pie (Android 9) are available.{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\n==Models==\n\nThe Moto G4 is available in a standard model, as well as the '''Moto G4 Play''' and '''Moto G4 Plus'''. The Play is a low-end model with reduced specifications, as well as an 8-megapixel camera and 720p display. The Plus model is a high-end version that features a 16-megapixel camera with dual-tone flash and infrared auto-focus, as well as an integrated fingerprint reader, up to 4&nbsp;GB of RAM, and up to 64&nbsp;GB of internal storage.<ref name=\"ars-motog4\">{{cite web|title=New Moto G lineup brings 1080p and fingerprint sensors to mid-range phones|url=https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2016/05/new-moto-g-lineup-brings-1080p-and-fingerprint-sensors-to-midrange-phones/|website=Ars Technica|accessdate=17 May 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"verge-g4\" />\n\nThe G4 and G4 Play were also sold as part of [[Amazon.com]]'s ''Prime Exclusive'' program, which offered a discounted version of the phone to [[Amazon Prime]] subscribers, subsidized by the display of personalized advertising on the [[lock screen]]. Due to this, the Prime Exclusive models of the device are ineligible for Motorola's [[bootloader]] unlocking program.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2016/09/06/moto-g4-play-amazon-ad-injected-prime-exclusive/|title=Moto G4 Play joins Amazon's ad-injected Prime phone deals|website=Engadget|language=en|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.androidpolice.com/2016/07/20/motorola-confirms-the-bootloader-on-the-amazon-prime-exclusive-moto-g4-cant-be-unlocked/|title=Motorola confirms the bootloader on the Amazon Prime Exclusive Moto G4 can't be unlocked|date=2016-07-20|website=Android Police|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/amazons-150-moto-g4-is-an-even-better-deal-than-the-original-hands-on/|last=Dolcourt|first=Jessica|website=CNET|title=Amazon's $150 Moto G4 is an even better deal than the original (hands-on)|date=20 July 2016|accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Model comparison ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Stat\n! colspan=2| Moto G4 Play<ref name=\"Moto G4 Play USA\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.motorola.com/us/products/moto-g-play|title=Moto G Play - Unlocked Android Smartphone|last=|first=|date=|website=Motorola - Unlocked Android Smartphones|publisher=Motorola Mobility LLC|access-date=29 June 2016}}</ref>\n! Moto G4<ref name=\"Moto G4 USA\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.motorola.com/us/products/moto-g|title=Moto G - Unlocked Android Smartphone|last=|first=|date=|website=Motorola - Unlocked Android Smartphones|publisher=Motorola Mobility LLC|access-date=29 June 2016}}</ref